body:
What my Gendrya ass needs for 8x04

  • Arya and Gendry looking for each other after the war, not knowing if the other is alive
  • Arya and Gendry hugging
  • Arya telling Gendry that she killed the Night King
  • Gendry being so proud of his girl
  • Arya and Gendry talking about the weapon he made for her
  • Arya and Gendry leaving the feast together
  • Arya and Gendry kissing (at least, we know this is really going to happen)
  • Arya and Gendry talking about their banging
  • Arya and Gendry discussing about their relationship and their feelings
  • Gendry calling Arya “Mylady” again
  • Arya and Gendry telling about their relationship to Jon, Sansa, Davos and The Hound (not Bran, cause he already knows…)
  • Sansa and Davos being so happy for them, Jon being protective but happy, The Hound being the Hound and being grumpy, but satisfied
  • Arya asking for Gendry to be legitimazed
  • Arya and Gendry being happy

Am is asking too much ?

For sure, but a girl can dream.

title: Arya will be fine
body:
“Live” I just looked at her and said, “Live.” And then, boom — he’s gone. But he doesn’t get to say it [in the episode], and he doesn’t need to say it. Life has been his whole struggle through the series.

summary: am I the only one who doesn’t really want arya to be pregnant right away? like I wouldn’t hate it if they go that route but idk...
body: am I the only one who doesn’t really want arya to be pregnant right away? like I wouldn’t hate it if they go that route but idk I liked that it was just her first time and the focus was on that and how she chose to be with him instead of just automatically getting her pregnant. I kind of like that it’s just them two (for now) and I don’t think every woman who has sex on a show needs to end up pregnant. I can totally see them just deciding to travel and discover new places and enjoy their time together when the show ends + I don’t think it’s necessary to make her a mother asap.

tags: made better sense in my head
body:
Game of Thrones Theory

Ok stay with me here

1. The Night King was a Targaryen. The first Targaryens were Dragon riders, which could be why the children chose one as there protector. Also Dragonglass both makes and destroys the White Walkers. Dragonglass comes from Dragonstone, the seat of house Targaryen. Also Valyrian steel can kill them which is “forged by dragon fire”.

2. The first Azor Ahai was a Stark. There home is called Winterfell which could be named after there greatest fet. It’s also the first stronghold the Night King would/does run into(besides Castle Black). They chose to be in the north to help defend the world. There motto “Winter is coming” a warning about the Night King passed down from generation to generation.

3. Only a Stark can defeat the Night King. “There must always be a Stark in Winterfell” besides being their home they never truly explain why… this also explains why SPOILER ALERT Arya kills him instead of Jon Snow or someone else. The Night King is fascinated by Jon Snow because he is both Targaryen and a Stark. Arya is a true Stark and the only one left with training to be able to do it. Bran being both crippled and the Three-eyeed Raven, Sansa being a more political figure then fighter.

Any thoughts?
